Dear David Ellis West Parents and Caregivers,
>>>>>>> master

We wanted to start by thanking you all as parents and caregivers for your fantastic support and patience. We are particularly appreciative of everything that you have been doing to support learning from home. We know how difficult it is to juggle working and supporting your own children with their online schooling, and this is of course in addition to dealing with all of the normal challenges of family life. We've received a number of messages of thanks and support from so many of you over these past few weeks, and these are all received very gratefully indeed. Thank you.

Please do remember to contact us if you need any support. In the meantime, we send our very best wishes to you and your families for a safe and successful school year.

Yours sincerely,

Maria Green
Tyron D. Hurd
Marcy Novak
Sharisse Spencer
Kimberleyn Williams

post_text:
David Ellis Academy West will be using a COVID-19 daily screening mobile app this school year called Fever Free. The app will monitor temperature and symptom checks. The app will allow them to do a privately recorded video temperature check of the child(ren) and symptom check prior to coming to school. If the child(ren) is fever and symptom-free, the app will show a “cleared for arrival” badge. This badge must be shown upon arrival at the school in order for the student to gain access to the building. If the child(ren) is not fever or symptom-free, the app will notify the parent that the child(ren) must remain home and give them further instructions.

In order to use the app, the parent must have a digital thermometer.

If 1 child is cleared for arrival, but one of the siblings is not, all of the children in that household must remain home and not report to the school. Further instructions will be given at that time.

The link below is a brief video you can show if you wish of how this easy user-friendly app works.

https://youtu.be/MGWD8L87Q5M

Return to Learn Zoom Meeting for Parents
Hello Parents,

As promised, we will be hosting parent meetings via Zoom to share information about the school’s learning models and action plans. The first Zoom meeting is scheduled for Thursday, August 6, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Online Learners only). The second Zoom meeting is scheduled for Friday, August 7, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Hybrid/In-Person Learners only).

There is no need to attend both of these Zoom Meetings days, as they will have different information specific to each learning model. We wanted to give a couple of different times that will work around your busy schedules. The information to access the Zoom meeting was sent to parents via email. Thank you for your participation and support. Stay safe and healthy!

Sincerely,

The David Ellis West Leadership Team

Zoom Meeting Schedule

Days/Times:
*Thurs., August 6, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Online Learners only).
*Fri., August 7, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Hybrid/In-Person Learners only).

Dear David Ellis West Parents,

Please be assured that we stand firm in our commitment to provide your child with a safe learning environment as well as a rigorous instructional program designed to meet the academic, social, and emotional needs of each and every student.

Join our virtual town hall meeting on Thursday, July 16, 2020, at 9:30 am, 1:30 pm, or 4:30 pm as we share our reopening goals (please check your email for the Zoom invite).

You're welcome to reach out to us anytime via email at thurd@deaschools.com or our Program Principal, Ms. Novak at mnovak@bardwellgroup.com.

Thank you for your continued support and positivity as we strive to do what is best for ALL of our students and employees during these challenging times.

Sincerely,

Marcy Novak
Program Principal of Curriculum & Instruction

Administrator of School Operations

Dear David Ellis West Parents,

Summertime is a fun and exciting time for students filled with outdoor activities and sports. But each year some students fall behind other classmates from summer reading loss. Oftentimes, families get too busy and forget to include reading into their busy schedules or children may not even have access to books.

Research has shown that summer reading loss is cumulative over time. While some struggling students are falling behind, others are moving ahead with their skills, creating a wider gap each year. By middle school, children who lose reading skills over the summer have accumulated a two‐year lag behind their classmates.

Hello David Ellis West Parents,

On Tuesday and Wednesday, July 14th and 15th between 8:30-11:30 a.m., families will be able to come to the school and pick up their child(ren)s’ items. This will be the final opportunity for families to pick up their children's field trip refunds, items left in the classroom and/or lockers, pre-ordered school shirts, and 8th-grade promotion certificates.

post_text:
Dear Class of 2020,

We know that the last 11 months may have gone too quickly for you, as they have for us! Due to COVID-19, we missed spending the last 3.5 months of school with you in person however, you and your loved ones have consistently been in our thoughts and prayers. You have changed a lot over the course of a year…more than you have even recognized yourself. The growth you have experienced this year is probably a little bit of a blur to you, but it's very evident to your parents and teachers. We're pleased to announce 100% of our 8th graders are promoted to high school.

You must decide now who you are going to be. As you enter high school, please don't ever forget who you are…

Hello DEAW Parents,

First, I pray that you're all doing well. As we prepare to officially end the 2019-2020 school year, we would like to see all of our students during our virtual assemblies on Thursday, June 4, 2020.

We will use this time to check-in with our students to ensure they're doing well (taking into consideration current events) and offer our support if needed.

The assembly schedule is as follows (please check your email for the Zoom invite).

K-2 @ 11:30 a.m.
3-5 @ 12:15 p.m.
6-8 @ 1:00 p.m.

Let me know if you any questions or concerns by reaching out to me by email at thurd@deaschools.com.

Sincerely,

Tyron D. Hurd
Administrator of School Operations

post_text:
Dear David Ellis West Parents,

Let me begin by saying how much we miss all of our students.

As you know, Governor Whitmer suspended “in-person instruction” for the remainder of the school year. The next month or so will not be easy. There will be mistakes, problems, and concerns along the way. However, there will be successes and celebrations! We understand many of you are still working and have several children to help, financial concerns, health issues, etc. We are here to patiently support you and our students throughout this challenging time. Frustrations are high due to our circumstances and we don’t want to increase the stress on our families.

We are going to continue to do our best…

March 23, 2020

To All DEAW Families,

We would like to thank you for your patience, understanding, and support as we journey through this ever-changing time in our community. We are grateful for your immediate call to action upon our decision to close the school. Our focus is on our students and their overall growth. Because of the uncertain nation-wide situation, we truly believe that the safest place for our students is at home with their families. Today Governor Whitmer issued a shelter in place which includes the closure of schools until April 14. This communication is to provide you with the latest information from the Michigan Department of Education Memo dated March 20, 2020… More

NO SCHOOL FOR STUDENTS - MARCH 13-APRIL 5, 2020

Good Morning DEAW Families,

Governor Whitmer announced the statewide closure of all K-12 school buildings from March 16 through April 5, 2020.

In addition, David Ellis Academy West will be closed today Friday, March 13 for students. Google Classroom will be an instrumental part of the online learning environment during the closure period. Therefore, staff members will be reporting to receive additional Google Classroom training.

Parents/Students are asked to visit the school today Friday, March 13, 2020 between 9:00-11:00 a.m. or 1:00-3:00 p.m. to pick up their belongings and to receive other important information.
We understand that this may be an inconvenience to some, so we apologize for the late notice.

Thank you for your understanding.

column1: The David Ellis Academy West Leadership Team"
link:
After-school Programing Canceled!

Dear David Ellis Academy West Families,

Please be advised that effective immediately the decision has been made to cancel all after-school activities including tutoring, STEM, robotics, choir, etc. and non-essential gatherings (field trips, Wax Museum, The Lion King play, basketball and volleyball games, etc.). We will continue to offer morning and afternoon KidZone service until further notice. Parents are asked to make the necessary arrangements to ensure their children are picked up on time at dismissal.

Thank you for your individual efforts to keep our students, staff, and your families safe. Moving forward our school will make determinations foremost on the safety and well-being of students, staff and our entire school community, and with the input of local and state officials. We thank you for your continued support and partnership as we address this situation together.

Best regards,

The David Ellis Academy West Leadership Team

Hello Parents,

On behalf of the staff, leadership team, and myself, we're looking forward to greeting our students tomorrow morning (barring any unforeseen circumstances).

Tomorrow, we'll proceed with our plans to celebrate Valentine's Day therefore, students may wear red, pink or white attire or their school shirts with black or blue (no ripped or torn) jeans.

Be safe, stay warm and drive carefully on the roads.

Best regards,

Tyron D. Hurd
Administrator of School Operations

Dear Parents,

Due to the winter weather advisory, the decision has been made to close school tomorrow Wednesday, February 26, 2020.

We do not take the decision to close school lightly. We value learning and recognize the impact that canceling school has on our students and families. The safety and wellbeing of our students, staff, and families are paramount in any decision to close the school.

Heavy snowfall and slippery roads will make for dangerous and unsafe travel conditions for our students and families.

Students are expected to log into their iReady and Kahn Academy accounts as well as complete work on their Science fair projects.

Be safe and have a good evening.

Sincerely,

Tyron D. Hurd

Dear Parents,

David Ellis Academy West will be closed tomorrow (Friday, February 14, 2020) due to a heating issue affecting our elementary wing. Please know that we do our best to keep our students and staff safe and comfortable at all times.

When it comes to the decision of whether the school should remain open or closed, there is no perfect decision upon which everyone will agree.

Thank you for your understanding and continued support.

Sincerely,

Tyron D. Hurd

Reading
• Phonological Awareness

post_text: DEAW's 5th grade jumped into the world of art, design, and electrical engineering today! They made simply beautiful Christmas Card Paper Circuits! A paper circuit is a low-voltage electronic circuit that is created on paper or cardboard using conductive copper tape, LEDs and a power source such as a coin-cell battery. Creating paper circuits is a good way to teach the basics of electricity and how circuits function. Through the Science, Math, & Artistic process they had to troubleshoot, investigate, practice patience, focus on the task, and use complex thinking! They were allowed to be creative & even listened to a little holiday music while they worked! Such a fun & festive day! Happy Holiday's! #STEMintegration #STEM #futureengineers Jessica James Amanda Ash Richard Rainville & Derek Zuidema
